Microalgae and cyanobacteria are huge natural sources of compounds of high nutritional and medicinal value. These marine and freshwater organisms are a rich source of bioactive compounds such as vitamins, proteins with essential amino acids, polysaccharides, fatty acids, minerals, photosynthetic pigments, enzymes, and fiber (
 Gogineni & Hamann, 2018; 
 Montalvao et al., 2016).
